dalvik.annotation
Annotation Type VirtualTestTarget

@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface VirtualTestTarget

Annotation for "virtual" implementation classes. These are classes that have the following attributes:

  • they implement a public interface or are a concrete implementation of a public abstract class,
  • they are not public,
  • instances can only be retrieved through some kind of factory method.

Example: MessageDigest is an abstract class. Concrete implementations of message digest algorithms such as MD5 and SHA-1 can only be retrieved through one of the static getInstance methods of MessageDigest, which accept the desired algorithm as a string parameter and return an implementation accordingly.

Even though the concrete implementation class for a message digest algorithm is not known, we need to be able to indicate that such a class exists and that it must be tested. This is done by defining corresponding classes and annotating them with @VirtualTestTarget. This class can then be used in the @TestTargetClass annotation with which we annotate TestCase subclasses.

Since:
Android 1.0
